  "title": "Senior Scientist, Ocean Systems",
  "description": "<p><strong>Roles and Responsibilities:</strong></p><p>Lead <strong>oceanographic & marine biogeochemical modelling</strong> to support <strong>environmental impact assessment</strong> and <strong>MRV</strong> of carbon‑removal processes. Shape modelling strategy, integrate field/lab/remote‑sensing data, and collaborate with engineering and policy stakeholders.</p><p><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Build/validate marine biogeochemical & transport models; quantify fluxes, baselines, and uncertainty.</li><li>Design MRV protocols and monitoring campaigns; integrate multi‑source datasets.</li><li>Advise on environmental impact assessments; engage external collaborators and verifiers.</li><li>Publish / internalised methods and results; mentor junior scientists.</li></ul><p><strong>Qualifications</strong></p><ul><li>PhD (or equivalent experience) in Oceanography, Marine Biogeochemistry, Earth/Environmental Science, or\nrelated.</li><li>7–10+ years in modelling and MRV for marine systems; track record of high‑quality outputs.</li><li>Proficiency in numerical modelling & data assimilation; statistical uncertainty quantification.</li></ul>",
